%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERemote%20work%20fueled%20about%2080%2C000%20extra%20US%20births%20annually%20between%202021%20and%202025%2C%20new%20research%20shows.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWorking%20from%20home%20one%20day%20a%20week%20boosts%20the%20odds%20of%20conception%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Stanford%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E'It's%20hard%20to%20conceive%20by%20email%2C'%20one%20of%20the%20report's%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20three-hour%20round-trip%20commute%20made%20motherhood%20and%20a%20career%20seem%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20Stefi%20Markowicz.%20But%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20she%20started%20working%20from%20home%2C%20and%20in%20June%20of%20this%20year%2C%20she%20gave%20birth%20to%20a%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkowicz%2C%2027%2C%20of%20Fort%20Lauderdale%2C%20Florida%2C%20credits%20the%20change%20in%20her%20routine%20to%20her%20becoming%20a%20mother%20earlier%20in%20life%20than%20anticipated.%20Research%20suggests%20other%20parents%20can%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20study%20from%20Stanford%20University%20estimates%20that%2080%2C000%20additional%20births%20occurred%20each%20year%20in%20the%20US%20between%202021%20and%202025%20due%20to%20a%20pandemic-fueled%20rise%20in%20remote-%20and%20hybrid-work%20arrangements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20found%20that%20couples%20who%20telecommute%20at%20least%20one%20day%20a%20week%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20conceive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20plan%20to%20have%20more%20children%20in%20the%20future%20%E2%80%94%20than%20those%20who%20go%20into%20an%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20are%20based%20on%20survey%20data%20from%2019%2C000%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eworkers%20in%2038%20countries%20and%20births%20reported%20between%202021%20and%202025.%20They%20also%20show%20that%20the%20likelihood%20of%20fertility%20is%20higher%20even%20when%20only%20one%20spouse%20or%20domestic%20partner%20works%20from%20home%20at%20least%20one%20day%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20at%20home%20all%20day%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20look%20after%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stanford%20professor%20Nicholas%20Bloom%2C%20who%20co-authored%20the%20study%20with%20Ph.D.%20student%20Katelyn%20Cranney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelecommuting%20also%20gives%20couples%20more%20time%20and%20energy%20to%20do%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20have%20children%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20added%20Bloom.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20conceive%20by%20email%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2224a7d565-01bb-472e-a8cf-6291002a5603%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBirth-rate%20bump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202019%20and%202021%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20primarily%20working%20from%20home%20tripled%20to%2017.9%25%2C%20or%20about%2028%20million%20workers%2C%20US%20Census%20Bureau%20data%20show.%20The%20Stanford%20study%20suggests%20that%20sharp%20rise%20in%20remote%20work%2C%20a%20byproduct%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20is%20largely%20responsible%20for%20the%20uptick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20come%2C%20however%2C%20as%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20employers%20are%20requiring%20workers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ceo-return-to-office-mandate-5-days-week-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20full-time%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20their%20mother%20ships%2C%20including%20Amazon%2C%20Dell%2C%20and%20JP%20Morgan%20Chase.%20Others%20are%20cutting%20back%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-creep-employers-increasing-rto-days-office-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enumber%20of%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20allow%20remote%20work.%20In%20the%20third%20quarter%20that%20ended%20in%20September%2C%20office%20vacancy%20rates%20declined%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20early%202019%2C%20according%20to%20JLL%2C%20a%20commercial%20real-estate%20services%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20and%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk%20have%20expressed%20interest%20in%20finding%20ways%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-states-federal-transportation-money-birth-marriage-rates-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboost%20birth%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20which%20had%20been%20declining%20for%20years%20until%202024.%20Last%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eyear%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-birth-rate-increase-moms-over-30-40-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20rate%20increased%20slightly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20CDC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20reasons%20why%20some%20Americans%20choose%20not%20to%20have%20children%2C%20including%20high%20childcare%20costs%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Febs%2Ffactsheets%2Ffamily-leave-benefits-fact-sheet.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520March%25202023%252C%252027%2520percent%2520of%2520civilian%2C89%2520had%2520access%2520to%2520unpaid%2520family%2520leave.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparental%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Stanford%20study%20suggests%20that%20remote%20work%20and%20hybrid%20schedules%20could%20help%20drive%20change%2C%20though%20there%20are%20other%20potential%20catalysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20report%2C%20from%20the%20Institute%20for%20Family%20Studies%2C%20a%20conservative%20think%20tank%2C%20suggests%20U.S.%20fertility%20rates%20could%20rise%20if%20couples%20had%20access%20to%20larger%20apartments.%20Based%20on%20a%20May%20survey%20of%20more%20than%206%2C000%20US%20adults%2C%20the%20results%20show%20that%20demand%20for%20family-size%20units%20far%20exceeds%20supply.%20Further%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%20respondents%20who%20said%20they%20favor%20larger%20floor%20plans%20also%20said%20that%20having%20more%20bedrooms%20would%20make%20them%20feel%20more%20ready%20to%20have%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e11818dc-0f89-4c8f-abd9-95cf2ad3ef20%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20quality%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20pandemic%20took%20hold%20in%20early%202020%2C%20Markowicz%20was%20commuting%20by%20car%20at%20least%20three%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20to%20and%20from%20her%20then-employer's%20office%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20she%20couldn't%20picture%20herself%20becoming%20a%20mom%20without%20having%20to%20quit%20her%20job%2C%20and%20her%20career%20in%20public%20relations%20was%20just%20getting%20started.%20She%20figured%20motherhood%20was%20a%20long%20way%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkowicz's%20vision%20of%20the%20future%2C%20however%2C%20would%20soon%20undergo%20a%20dramatic%20change.%20Like%20many%20people%2C%20she%20responded%20to%20the%20pandemic%20by%20relocating%20closer%20to%20family.%20She%20took%20up%20residence%20in%20her%20parents'%20Fort%20Lauderdale%20home%20and%20continued%20working%20for%20her%20employer%20from%20her%20childhood%20bedroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20year%20later%2C%20Markowicz%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20a%20man%20she%20met%20on%20Hinge%2C%20and%20in%20late%202022%2C%20they%20got%20married.%20By%20then%2C%20she'd%20changed%20jobs%2C%20and%20her%20new%20employer%20supported%20remote%20work%2C%20while%20her%20husband%2C%20a%20construction-management%20professional%2C%20had%20a%20hybrid%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarkowicz%20suddenly%20realized%20she%20could%20become%20the%20kind%20of%20working%20mom%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20one%20who's%20always%20close%20to%20her%20child%20and%20not%20too%20tired%20from%20commuting%20to%20juggle%20parenthood%20and%20a%20career.%20She%20and%20her%20husband%20decided%20to%20try%20to%20conceive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20much%20easier%20to%20think%20about%20raising%20a%20family%20without%20the%20stresses%20of%20leaving%20your%20house%20every%20single%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Markowicz.%20%26quot%3BYou%20also%20have%20more%20energy%20left%20for%20quality%20time%20with%20your%20partner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%202024%2C%20she%20found%20out%20she%20was%20pregnant.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20she%20was%20laid%20off.%20Rather%20than%20job-hunting%20and%20explaining%20she'd%20soon%20need%20to%20go%20on%20maternity%20leave%2C%20she%20started%20her%20own%20PR%20agency%20from%20home.%20Now%20a%20first-time%20mom%2C%20she%20relies%20on%20a%20day-care%20center%20and%20her%20mother%20to%20watch%20her%20son%20while%20she%20works%2C%20though%20both%20babysitters%20are%20a%20short%20distance%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20I%20would%20be%20able%20to%20do%20what%20I'm%20doing%20right%20now%20if%20I%20had%20to%20commute%20to%20an%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Markowicz%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20expects%20to%20be%20expecting%20again%20in%20the%20future%2C%20as%20long%20as%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20and%20her%20husband%20can%20hold%20onto%20their%20flexible%20work%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20definitely%20want%20to%20have%20another%20kid%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextra-births-align-with-work-from-home-stanford-study-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1761297901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68fa3f9a0be9845f2dc4f57a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextra-births-align-with-work-from-home-stanford-study-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Couples%20who%20telecommute%20at%20least%20one%20day%20a%20week%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20conceive%20than%20those%20who%20go%20into%20an%20office%20five%20days%2C%20new%20research%20shows.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sneedleman%40businessinsider.com%20(Sarah%20E.%20Needleman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextra-births-al