rs%2C%20options%2C%20and%20alcohol%20content%20levels.%20But%20craft%20beer%20maybe%20exploded%20a%20little%20%3Cem%3Etoo%20%3C%2Fem%3Emuch.%20The%20space%20has%20become%20very%20crowded%2C%20and%20brewers'%20flavors%20and%20names%20have%20gotten%20so%20outlandish%20that%20the%20sheer%20number%20of%20choices%20can%20become%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20craft%20beer%20market%20is%20kind%20of%20reaching%20a%20point%20of%20oversaturation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Garrett%20Nelson%2C%20an%20equity%20research%20analyst%20at%20CFRA%20Research.%20%26quot%3BThe%20last%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20there%20have%20been%20more%20breweries%20that%20have%20closed%20than%20new%20ones%20that%20have%20opened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20broader%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-cities-in-the-us-for-foodies-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efoodie%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20craft%20beer%20isn't%20necessarily%20pass%C3%A9%2C%20but%20it%20isn't%20special%2C%20either.%20It's%20been%20very%20democratized%E2%80%94%20anyone%20can%20snap%20a%20picture%20of%20their%20meal%20and%20post%20it%20on%20Instagram%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it's%20lost%20its%20sheen.%20And%20it%20codes%20millennial%2C%20which%20is%20now%20firmly%20code%20for%20%26quot%3Buncool.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20cultural%20signifier%20in%20the%20way%20it%20used%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kate%20Bernot%2C%20the%20lead%20analyst%20at%20Sightlines%2C%20which%20researches%20the%20alcohol%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20seemingly%20endless%20array%20of%20IPAs%20epitomizes%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-are-ipas-so-popular-2015-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecraft%20brewing%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20your%20hazy%2C%20your%20juicy%2C%20double%2C%20etc.%20But%20they're%20not%20for%20everyone.%20The%20alcohol%20content%20is%20often%20quite%20high%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can't%20really%20spend%20a%20day%20watching%20football%2C%20knocking%20back%20IPAs%20without%20being%20in%20for%20a%20wild%20time.%20Many%20people%20don't%20love%20their%20bitter%20flavor%2C%20either%2C%20and%20they'd%20prefer%20something%20that%20doesn't%20knock%20your%20socks%20off%20with%20hops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20American%20drinker%20has%20definitely%20shifted%2C%20if%20not%20toward%20blander%20stuff%2C%20necessarily%2C%20I%20would%20say%20much%20more%20straightforward%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dave%20Infante%2C%20who%20writes%20a%20newsletter%20about%20drinking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fingers.email%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20Fingers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Beyond%20beer%2C%20he%20points%20to%20ready-to-drink%20options%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-claw-is-not-a-beer-replacement-or-healthier-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhite%20Claw%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20High%20Noon%2C%20that%20are%20packaged%20in%20straight-to-the-point%20fruit%20flavors.%20Within%20beer%2C%20he%20mentions%20Michelob%20Ultra%2C%20which%20recently%20surpassed%20Modelo%20as%20America's%20top-selling%20brew.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20got%20an%20active%20lifestyle%20brand%20that%20gives%20it%20a%20big%20boost%2C%20and%20it%20isn't%20marketed%20aggressively%20on%20its%20flavor%20because%20it%20doesn't%20have%20a%20whole%20lot%20to%20offer%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Ultra's%20marketing%20profile%20is%20now%20so%20ubiquitous%20that%20the%20other%20big%20guys%20are%20taking%20a%20run%20at%20it.%20In%202020%2C%20Miller%20Lite%20ran%20an%20ad%20campaign%20against%20Michelob%20Ultra%2C%20boasting%20that%20it%20has%20more%20taste%20for%20just%20one%20more%20calorie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20stem%20the%20tide%2C%20more%20craft%20brewers%20are%20expanding%20their%20offerings%20in%20pilsners%20and%20lagers%20to%20capture%20a%20broader%20base%20of%20consumers%20and%20appeal%20to%20this%20back-to-basics%20palette.%20When%20considering%20the%20cost%20question%2C%20consumers%20tend%20to%20lean%20toward%20purchases%20that%20feel%20less%20risky%2C%20and%20lower-profile%2C%20more%20familiar%20flavors%20scratch%20that%20itch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESimplicity%20is%20a%20key%20part%20of%20Garage%20Beer's%20success.%20The%20brand%20grew%20out%20of%20a%20craft%20brewery%20in%20the%20Midwest%20and%20has%20now%20struck%20out%20on%20its%20own.%20The%20light%20beer%20has%20a%204%25%20ABV%2C%20comes%20in%20a%20white%2C%20unremarkable%20can%2C%20and%20is%20about%20as%20basic%20as%20you%20can%20get%20in%20its%20branding%3A%20the%20garage.%20It%20comes%20in%20two%20flavors%20%E2%80%94%20regular%20and%20lime.%20NFL%20star%20brothers%20Jason%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-is-travis-kelce-net-worth-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETravis%20Kelce%3C%2Fa%3E%20invested%20in%20Garage%20in%202024%20and%20do%20ads%20for%20it%20that%20can%20be%20borderline%20boorish.%20Its%20ad%20spots%20include%20spoofs%20of%20old%20martial%20arts%20movies%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravis-kelce-jason-kelce-brothers-brand-tv-clothing-endorsements-podcast-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJason%20Kelce%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20partnerships%20with%20pro%20wrestlers%20doing%20body%20slams%20and%20grilling%20burgers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20going%20back%20to%20beer's%20roots%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20where%20it%20was%20endorsed%20by%20sports%20players%2C%20it's%20easy%20drinking%2C%20and%20it's%20for%20your%20garage%2C%26quot%3B%20Sightlines'%20Bernot%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20course%20correction%20to%20the%20fanciness%20of%20craft%20and%20fan%20imports.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarage%20Beer%20reportedly%20reached%20a%20%24200%20million%20valuation%20and%20expects%20to%20produce%20250%2C000%20barrels%20this%20year%2C%20although%20that%20still%20makes%20it%20a%20tiny%20fish%20in%20the%20giant%20beer%20sea.%20(For%20some%20context%2C%20the%20US%20beer%20industry%20produces%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20barrels%20annually.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20Sauer%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Garage%20Beer%2C%20who%20acquired%20the%20company%20in%202023%2C%20tells%20me%20they%20hope%20to%20%26quot%3Bbring%20folks%20back%20to%20beer%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20beer-positive%2C%20independent%20message.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20take%20ourselves%20seriously%20in%20any%20way%2C%20shape%2C%20or%20form.%20We%20just%20try%20to%20be%20the%20dumbest%20beer%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20and%20that's%20sort%20of%20the%20spirit%20of%20what%20beer%20has%20been%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20small%20names%2C%20such%20as%20Montucky%20Cold%20Snacks%20and%20Easy%20Rider%2C%20are%20also%20making%20waves%20by%20tapping%20into%20nostalgic%20themes%20and%20retro%20aesthetics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20liquid%20inside%20the%20can%20is%20not%20very%20remarkable.%20It's%20fine.%20It's%20a%20commodity%20lager%20more%20or%20less%2C%26quot%3B%20Infante%20says.%20%26quot%3BThose%20products%20are%20mostly%20marketing%2C%20and%20they've%20been%20very%20successful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20beer%20industry%20is%20facing%20a%20conundrum%20that%2C%20although%20not%20existential%2C%20is%20nonetheless%20challenging.%20It%20needs%20to%20appeal%20to%20more%20consumers%2C%20especially%20as%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falcohol-year-unhealthy-moderate-drinking-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrow%20wary%20of%20alcohol%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20have%20more%20drinking%20options%20when%20they%20do%20decide%20to%20imbibe.%20And%20any%20efforts%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20potential%20new%20drinkers%20come%20with%20some%20downsides%20in%20this%20fraught%20cultural%20moment%3A%20In%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanheuser-busch-ceo-response-bud-light-dylan-mulvaney-can-sales-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBud%20Light%3C%2Fa%3E%20sent%20a%20few%20cans%20of%20beer%20to%20a%20transgender%20influencer%20as%20part%20of%20an%20attempt%20to%20reach%20that%20community%2C%20and%2C%20well%2C%20you%20probably%20remember%20where%20that%20landed.%20Companies%20need%20to%20duke%20it%20out%20with%20their%20competitors%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20afraid%20of%20land%20mines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20very%20competitive%20market%20right%20now%20because%20there's%20no%20growth%2C%20and%20so%20when%20there's%20no%20growth%2C%20it's%20a%20market%20share%20battle%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Gary%20Wilcox%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20communications%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%20who's%20studied%20alcohol%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeer%20advertising%20isn't%20as%20vapid%2C%20silly%2C%20or%20sexist%20as%20it%20used%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20beer%20brands%20don't%20generally%20do%20the%20hot%20women%20running%20around%20in%20wet%20T-shirts%20thing%20like%20they%20did%20in%20the%20past.%20But%20it's%20not%20really%20thrilling%2C%20either.%20The%20themes%20are%20basically%20America%2C%20garages%2C%20barbeques%2C%20beaches%2C%20and%20gentle%20reminders%20to%20consumers%20that%20they%20exist.%20Bud%20Light's%20most%20recent%20Super%20Bowl%20campaign%20features%20singer%20Post%20Malone%2C%20comedian%20Shane%20Gillis%2C%20and%20former%20NFL%20star%20Peyton%20Manning%20at%20backyard%20parties%2C%20sitting%20in%20driveways%2C%20and%20screwing%20around%20on%20the%20porch.%20Over%20the%20summer%2C%20Miller%20Lite%20launched%20a%20commercial%20celebrating%20its%2050th%20anniversary%20that%20highlighted%20its%20history%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bbackyard%20beer.%26quot%3B%20Beer's%20back%20to%20be%20positioned%20for%20regular%20guys%20%E2%80%94%20the%20group%20that's%20historically%20been%20viewed%20as%20pretty%20inoffensive%20in%20marketing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBernot%20says%20beer%20marketing%20is%20more%20%26quot%3Bboring%26quot%3B%20than%20it's%20ever%20been.%20%26quot%3BThere%20hasn't%20been%20an%20iconic%20beer%20marketing%20campaign%20that%20I%20can%20think%20of%20in%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Budweiser%20still%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwatch-budweisers-clydesdale-super-bowl-ad-starring-a-7-day-old-foal-2013-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClydesdale%20horses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Corona%20has%20been%20using%20the%20%26quot%3Bfind%20your%20beach%26quot%3B%20slogan%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20Coors%20Light's%20schtick%20remains%20that%20it's%20%E2%80%A6%20cold.%20%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20seen%20beer%20lead%20the%20cultural%20and%20advertising%20conversation%20the%20way%20it%20used%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaste-wise%2C%20beer's%20current%20trajectory%20could%20be%20considered%20a%20reversion%20to%20the%20norm.%20Your%20boomer%20dad%20wasn't%20knocking%20back%20sour%20beers%20after%20work%2C%20he%20was%20grabbing%20a%20Bud.%20Tastes%20going%20back%20from%20fancy%20to%20no-frills%20may%20have%20been%20somewhat%20inevitable.%20And%20with%20the%20marketing%2C%20the%20goal%20seems%20to%20be%20to%20make%20as%20few%20waves%20as%20possible%2C%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20we're%20here%2C%20but%20also%2C%20there's%20nothing%20to%20see%20here.%26quot%3B%20And%20the%20best%20way%20to%20do%20that%2C%20for%20now%2C%20appears%20to%20be%20for%20brands%20to%20do%20some%20dumbing%20down.%20The%20problem%20is%2C%20in%20working%20so%20hard%20not%20to%20offend%20or%20confuse%2C%20beer%20is%20losing%20some%20of%20the%20irreverence%20that%20once%20made%20it%20fun%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%